<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Open UV</title>
</head>
<body>
    <%- include('partials/header.ejs') %>
    
    <% if(locals.data){ %>
        <h1>UV Index: <%= locals.uvIndex %> (<%= uvLevel %>) </h1>
        <h2>Current UV Today: <%= locals.uvMaxIndex %> at <%= locals.maxUV %></h2>

        <h3>Sunrise: <%=locals.sunrise%></h3>
        <h3>Sunset: <%= locals.sunset %></h3>
        <h4>Safe Exposure Times:</h4>
        <ul>
            <li>Skin Type 1: Very fair, red/blonde hair, freckles. Time Before Burn: <%= data.safe_exposure_time.st1 %> minutes. Extreme caution â€“ burn almost immediately</li>
            <li>Skin Type 2: Fair skin, burns easily. Time Before Burn: <%= data.safe_exposure_time.st2 %> minutes. Use sunscreen, avoid midday sun</li>
            <li>Skin Type 3: Light to light brown skin. Time Before Burn: <%= data.safe_exposure_time.st3 %> minutes. Sunscreen and shade highly recommended</li>
            <li>Skin Type 4: Olive or medium brown skin. Time Before Burn: <%= data.safe_exposure_time.st4 %> minutes. Still at risk, especially face/shoulders</li>
            <li>Skin Type 5: Dark brown skin. Time Before Burn: <%= data.safe_exposure_time.st5 %> minutes. Lower risk, but UV damage still occurs</li>
            <li>Skin Type 6: Deeply pigmented dark skin. Time Before Burn: <%= data.safe_exposure_time.st6 %> minutes. Least risk of burning, but sunscreen still advised for long exposure</li>
        </ul>
    <% } else if(locals.error){ %>
            <%= error %>
        <% } %>
            
        <%- include('partials/footer.ejs') %>
</body>
</html>